Cloudformation is one of the most popular and widely used IAC from AWS. Essentially you design or download a template (blueprint) that meets your requirements. The template can is broken down into various parts:
Templates are created in two languages. They are JSON and YAML. YAML is the most commonly used due to the fact that it is easier to read and write.
The "anatomoy of an ec2.yml template is: 
-Desceription- this literally describes what you want Cloudformation to do.
-Parameter:
-Mapping:
-Conditions:
-Resources: The heart of the template. Without this properly set the entire template won't work.
-Outputs:
